# Skill: Accessibility and QA

Use this skill before finishing any UI task or when improving semantic HTML, keyboard support, focus states, and final polish.

## Accessibility Rules
- Use semantic HTML wherever possible.
- Use real buttons for actions.
- Use links for navigation.
- Add `aria-label` to icon-only controls.
- Make focus states visible with `:focus-visible`.
- Ensure overlays and drawers can be closed with Escape.
- Ensure language toggle, search, mobile menu, and back-to-top are keyboard usable.
- Do not rely on color alone to communicate state.

## QA Checklist
Before considering a task complete, verify:
- `index.html` loads without build tools.
- Bangla mode renders correctly.
- English mode renders correctly.
- Language toggle works after re-render.
- Search overlay works.
- Mobile drawer works.
- Back-to-top works.
- Scroll reveal does not break layout.
- No horizontal overflow on mobile.
- No browser console errors during normal use.
- CSS comments and JS comments are useful.

## Code Cleanup Rules
- Remove dead CSS only when clearly unused.
- Avoid deleting existing features unintentionally.
- Keep comments concise and helpful.
- Keep function names descriptive.
- Do not introduce large unstructured blocks of code.

## Definition of Done
A UI task is complete only when the feature looks polished, works in both languages, remains static, and is safe to preview by opening `index.html`.
